2nd Gen Toyota 4Runner SR5 3.0 V6 for sale   *UPDATED (forgot to mention certain things)  Things that have been replaced:  - CV Axle - Brake Booster - Alternator - Spark Plugs - Driver side Turn signal light and Brake light - Has good tags (expire in June 2021)  Things that work:   - Almost all Interior lighting - All Exterior lighting - 4wd - All windows roll up and down including rear - All Doors lock - All windshield wipers work  Issues:  - Factory cup holder is missing - Heater does not work(AC somehow does though), is most likely caused by a messed up hose that I never bothered to replace - Hood does not shut all the way - Has automatic transmission, if you want to unlock full potential of this vehicle consider a manual swap. - Slow vehicle in general. Not my fault, however, blame Toyota for making a V6 motor that only made 150hp out of the factory the same years they were making Supras and Celicas. - Radio is all wacked out, Aux to cassette adapter is stuck in tape player, and it has no antenna. - Tons of dents/paint fading all around it, however, none of them resulted in any suspension issues - No rear bumper - Odometer came disconnected during a previous ownership, was able to get it plugged back in, however I still have no clue how far it had been driven before I fixed the issue(reason for odometer broken) - Single interior light does not function, is the least important one anyway -Speedometer cable has been snapped  I am selling this vehicle mainly because I just plain don't want it anymore, and I need something more efficient in general. The engine runs good, recently did a engine treatment that worked better than I thought it would. The transmission works and most likely will for a long time, it just sucks because the automatics in this generation of 4Runners' were all 4-speeds compared to the 5-speed manual. Price is relative to the amount of money put into vehicle. I would recommend this as a weekend off-roader/ project car.

And the Check engine light is on due to a PO420 Code. This means the catalytic converter is not functioning efficiently, therefore increasing the output of harmful pollutants by the vehicle. Look through all the pics. See some of the most recent big-money repairs. OBO.

2001 740i  This is a excellent 2001 740i M Sport.   The car spent most of its life in CA, was brought to the Chicagoland area and had one owner which I bought it from.  The previous owner (PO) did many updates to the car.  The car was stylized to represent a 740i in Germany not one that was sold in the NA market.  Hence the Euro plate on the front.    Look close - there are not many typical issues with the car.  When issues arose items and parts where repaired or replaced through the life of the car.  You will find this car in very fine condition.  In addition the M62TU has just had engine guides, Vanos replacement, gaskets, filters, fluids many parts and hours of service. The time has come to finally sell our beloved California dream, T.REX. A fair bird from the early 70s designed specifically for Campers. We bought her in 2013 when we moved to California as a weekend adventure get away. We have adventured with her all across northern California (Tahoe, Bodega Bay, Yosemite, Big Sur, Napa and more). We have decided to move and unfortunately cannot bring the camper with us. Both the camper and the Ford are stored in Half Moon bay in a storage unit.  **General Information about truck & camper:** TRUCK:  -1973 Ford F350 SuperCamper -Dimensions camper + truck: 25 feet long X 7 feet wide X 10.25 Feet Tall (including 12 inch roof rack) -Incredible sound system with amplifiers behind seats - worth 1.5k alone -CD player with USB plug-in -In the last 2 years, we FIXED the timing belt, radiator, chain kit, distributer, and transmission accumulator - since then we have done routine maintenance (oil changes) every 2,800 miles and fix things if they break now and then. -Truck (F3250 Super Camper) does not currently reliably run, and needs some work to make sure its running consistently. -8-10 MPG -Green and blue exterior / green leather and fabric interior with wood trim (in great condition) -~150,000 miles CAMPER: -Great lighting, tons of windows -In 1973, Ford Motor Company and Starcraft RV partnered to develop and manufacture the American Road, a truck camper decades ahead of its time. -44+ years after the debut, the American Road remains a unique and compelling statement in truck camper history. From its smart floor plan, to the fiberglass shell construction, to the use of basement holding tanks, the American Road design could be considered competitive with the non-slide truck campers in production today. -Not sure if water, heater/air conditioner etc work, we have only used the propane for the fridge and stove/oven which work well -Three burner stove and oven works well -Nordic fridge does not currently work (free large size cooler you can use inside camper if you purchase it) -Comes with brand new 8 inch memory foam full size mattress (we used this new one 1x in 2019) -Very high ceiling - great for tall people -People typically buy these and remodel them (gut everything and start fresh) - to each their own  PRICE:  Willing to sell truck and camper topper separately but you will have to pay for someone to take the camper off the truck. -Camper topper: $2,000 -Truck: $1,000  ***Text me if you are interested in purchasing (six.five.zero.seven.nine.six.six.one.six.zero). I am available Thursdays between 3:30 PM - 6:30 PM - let me know what time works for you during that time frame/day. We are selling one of our work trucks, and it has been a great small truck for smaller properties especially in the city of Erie. Not too many places you can't get into with this truck and plow set up.  The plow is a light weight blizzard plow but it is still commercial grade.  The value of the plow according to the dealer is $2,000 to $2,500 we are asking $2,500 in this price.    The truck has 4 WD works, button push and power windows. The truck will come with the tool box in the picture and tranny working good.  A Few dings on the body but in pretty good shape.  Inside is clean no smoking was allowed.    It is inspected up to May 2021 and worked well for us all winter. We put some new tires on it in January.    We are also selling at 2001 Ford Ranger and plow and a regular bed 2001 Chevy 1500 with heavy duty blizzard plow if you want more or something different.  We also have some plow accounts and routes that we are selling for next winter. If you are looking to buy some plow trucks and earn some good money we may have the customers already under contract for you. We are selling around 50 accounts that generate $500 per plow for $5,000. We can do a package deal with any of the trucks we have for sale too.
